              <p class="c-article-rights"><a data-track="click" data-track-action="view rights and permissions" data-track-label="link" href="https://s100.copyright.com/AppDispatchServlet?title=Alendronate%20use%20and%20bone%20mineral%20density%20gains%20in%20women%20with%20moderate-severe%20%28stages%203B%E2%80%935%29%20chronic%20kidney%20disease%3A%20an%20open%20cohort%20multivariable%20and%20propensity%20score%20analysis%20from%20Funen%2C%20Denmark&amp;author=M.%20Sanni%20Ali%20et%20al&amp;contentID=10.1007%2Fs11657-020-00746-z&amp;copyright=The%20Author%28s%29&amp;publication=1862-3522&amp;publicationDate=2020-06-01&amp;publisherName=SpringerNature&amp;orderBeanReset=true&amp;oa=CC%20BY">Reprints and permissions</a></p></div></div></section><section aria-labelledby="article-info" data-title="About this article"><div class="c-article-section" id="article-info-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="article-info">About this article</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="article-info-content"><div class="c-bibliographic-information"><div class="u-hide-print c-bibliographic-information__column c-bibliographic-information__column--border"><a data-crossmark="10.1007/s11657-020-00746-z" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://crossmark.crossref.org/dialog/?doi=10.1007/s11657-020-00746-z" data-track="click" data-track-action="Click Crossmark" data-track-label="link" data-test="crossmark"><img loading="lazy" width="57" height="81" alt="Check for updates. Verify currency and authenticity via CrossMark" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,"></a></div><div class="c-bibliographic-information__column"><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="citeas">Cite this article</h3><p class="c-bibliographic-information__citation">Ali, M.S., Ernst, M., Robinson, D.E. <i>et al.</i> Alendronate use and bone mineral density gains in women with moderate-severe (stages 3B–5) chronic kidney disease: an open cohort multivariable and propensity score analysis from Funen, Denmark.
